  <scopecontent id="aspace_5e352d7ea82033304c44c0f3f31645bb">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Reports and studies deriving from Nixon's work as a consulting economist with particular reference to the Hong Kong Airport, Cairo water studies, and other projects. Also includes early files on New York State economy and politics, 1950s; "Research Memoranda" from the Committee for Economic Development, Area Development Division by Nixon and others, 1960s; works on real estate indexation, 1990s; and speeches and articles.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_b7d3f6c786b8e43fa607147137c2d041">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>John H. Nixon papers, #6336. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
